iter39 (2026-05-26): baked two config changes into the shipped gm-skill SKILL.md per user. (1) STANDING APPROVAL rule added (after Done-is-plugkits-pronouncement): every further session is pre-approved to finish ALL requested work - plan as written + additions joining along the way + any unfinished/newly-discovered work - at maximum granularity (one PRD row per real unit, every-possible applied to every noun); no stop-to-ask, no defer-reachable-work, no scope-narrowing; blockedBy:external ONLY for genuinely unreachable authority (another teams repo, hardware credential, someone-elses product decision), NEVER for large/tedious/multi-component/concurrently-contended work (rebase + land alongside). Codifies the iter38 lesson into the shipped skill so every LLM inherits it. (2) Removed the .js setup surface: allowed-tools frontmatter dropped Bash(node *), now Skill,Read,Write,Bash(bun *),Bash(npx *); setup is invoked via bun x (NOT bunx) or npx -y fallback only - the boot/recovery prose already used bun x/npx (verified bunx=0, node-.js-invocation=0). Propagation verified: package.json files[] includes skills/ so the edited skills/gm-skill/SKILL.md ships in npm gm-skill; publish.yml publish-gm-skill job npm-publishes + embeds SKILL.md into gm-plugkit (ensureSkillMdFresh); bootstrapPlugkit sha-refreshes installed ~/.agents+~/.claude skill copies. NOTE the orchestrator gate ENFORCED the new rule mid-edit: a prd-add containing the phrase "next session" was rejected (deviation prd-add deferral-language §22/§17) - fitting dogfood of the no-defer rule I was codifying.